            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>How do I check-in for a flight on Spirit Airlines? </h3>
            <p>
                <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/">Spirit Flights</a> passengers have various options to check in
                for their travel. Online check-in, accessible up to 24 hours before your trip, is the most practical
                option. Visit the Spirit Airlines website, input your confirmation code, or sign in to your account
                to check in online. You can also use the Spirit Airlines smartphone app to check-in.
            </p>
            <h3>Can I bring a musical instrument on board a Spirit Airlines flight? </h3>
            <p>
                As long as it can fit in the overhead compartment or beneath the seat before you, you can carry a
                musical instrument on board Spirit Airlines. You should buy an extra seat if your instrument is too
                big to fit in the overhead compartment or underneath the seat. The instrument must be properly
                wrapped and put in a hard-sided case. One personal item and carry-on luggage are also permitted per
                passenger on Spirit Airlines. For more details, check out their website's policy on musical
                instruments.
            </p>
            <h3>Does Spirit Airlines offer a student discount? </h3>
            <p>
                Spirit Airlines doesn't currently provide a student discount. They do, however, run additional sales
                and promotions all year round. Check their website or subscribe to their email for discounts and
                offers. Students can also reduce travel costs by making travel reservations in advance or going
                during off-peak hours.
            </p>
            <h3>Does Spirit Airlines offer lounge access? </h3>
            <p>
                Spirit Airlines does not provide access to lounges. They do not participate in lounge access programs
                or joint ventures with other airlines or lounge networks nor operate their airport lounges. To make
                your trip more enjoyable, they provide additional services and amenities, like assigned seating,
                priority boarding, and Wi-Fi on some flights.
            </p>
            <h3>Can I purchase travel insurance for my Spirit Airlines flight? </h3>
            <p>
                For your flight, you can get travel insurance through Spirit Airlines' partner, Allianz Global
                Assistance. Spirit Airlines offers a variety of travel insurance products to protect you against
                unforeseen circumstances that can interfere with your travel plans, including trip disruptions,
                cancellations, and medical emergencies. Your travel dates, location, and other considerations will
                affect the insurance options and pricing. Upon making a <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/spirit-airlines-deals.aspx">Spirit Airlines reservation</a>,
